threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered ransomware. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a sophisticated Trojan/Infostealer that employs dynamic API resolution to obfuscate its functionality. Key malicious behaviors include: 1) Anti-analysis/Environment targeting: sub_404819 checks for specific locale IDs (e.g., 0x419/Russian, 0x422/Ukrainian), a common tactic for Russian-origin malware to avoid infecting CIS countries. 2) Data Exfiltration: sub_404255 captures screen content, creates a .BMP file, and stores it for exfiltration. 3) C2 Communication: sub_4031ee implements an HTTP POST-based beaconing mechanism using custom encryption and Base64 encoding (alphabet found in sub_4012a4). 4) Reconnaissance: Multiple functions (sub_4067ad, sub_405bcc) implement recursive directory traversal for file harvesting.
